HEADWORD: Cerecloth
<hw>Cere"cloth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cera</ets> wax + E. <ets>cloth</ets>.]</ety> <def>A cloth smeared
with melted wax, or with some gummy or glutinous matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Linen, besmeared with gums, in manner of <qex>cerecloth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerement</ent>⟦br⟧
